<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Italian Andrea Montermini <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">signed</EVENT> for Formula One  team Simtek Ford on <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">Wednesday</TIMEX3> as a replacement for Roland Ratzenberger, who  <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">died</EVENT> in a crash at Imola at <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE">the end April</TIMEX3>.&#13;
Montermini, 29, will <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="FUTURE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">team</EVENT> up with David Brabham for the Grand Prix races  in Spain <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE">this weekend</TIMEX3> and Canada on <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE">June 12</TIMEX3>.&#13;
He has never taken part in a Formula One race but has test <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">driven</EVENT> for  Ferrari and Benetton.&#13;
The team has also <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">signed</EVENT> up French driver Jean-Marc Gounon, who has an  eight-race contract and will <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="FUTURE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">drive</EVENT> in the French Grand Prix in <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE">July</TIMEX3>.&#13;
